@HuntingStops @AdamRusch @Quantumplation @NicolasC3rny In the budget info action, we said we would not do yield farming. Largely because the goal is to increase liquidity into the ecosystem, and if we put LP tokens into farming contracts, it would take away from liquidity incentives for the ecosystem.

We also said we would hold all assets (ADA, stablecoins, LP coins) directly in the contract address so that it is easy for anyone to audit. This from the time the funds are withdrawn to the contract address from the treasury, you will be able to see every transaction that occurs, and because we will hold all assets in the treasury contract, it will be easy to find the total value of all holdings.

I am using the phraseology "we said in the budget info action..." not because we will do anything different, rather we are no longer bound to follow through on most of the budget components and promises we made in it. However, the governance protocol is still valid, and can only be changed by another successful info action. We are bound to comply with all the terms of that even though the specific budget info action is no longer relevant under the current constitution.

